# Production runtime requirements — INTENT file.
#
# Edit this file when adding or upgrading a runtime dependency.
# Then run:
#
#   make compile-deps
#
# That recompiles requirements.txt with full transitive deps + sha256
# hashes via ``pip-compile --generate-hashes``. Commit BOTH this file
# and the generated requirements.txt in the same PR.
#
# Pinning policy: exact ``==`` pins for every direct dep. The lock
# file (requirements.txt) is what production installs from; this
# file is the human-readable intent. Floating ``>=`` here would
# defeat the purpose of the lock — every recompile would silently
# pull whatever's newest.
#
# PT-v4-r1-060: the hashes in requirements.txt close the
# OpenSSF Pinned-Dependencies gap (a re-published-under-the-same-
# version PyPI compromise can no longer slip into a Reverto install).

